        <h1>LeetCode 1493: Longest Subarray of 1's After Deleting One Element (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a binary array nums, you should delete one element from it. Return the size of the longest
                non-empty subarray containing only 1's in the resulting array. Return 0 if there is no such subarray.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,1,0,1]<br>
                Output: 3<br>
                Explanation: After deleting the number in position 2, [1,1,1] contains 3 numbers with value of 1's.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int longestSubarray(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int left = 0;
        int zerosCount = 0;
        int maxLength = 0;
        
        // Sliding window approach
        for (int right = 0; right &lt; n; right++) {
            // Expand window by including current element
            if (nums[right] == 0) {
                zerosCount++;
            }
            
            // Shrink window if we have more than 1 zero
            while (zerosCount &gt; 1) {
                if (nums[left] == 0) {
                    zerosCount--;
                }
                left++;
            }
            
            // Update maximum length
            // We subtract 1 because we must delete exactly one element
            maxLength = max(maxLength, right - left + 1 - 1);
        }
        
        return maxLength;
    }
};</code></pre>
